<h4>Homework (Due Tuesday Sept 10)</h4>

<ol>
<li>Transform your text file from last week into a web page. At a
minimum, you should use several different header tags (&lt;h1>,
&lt;h2>, etc), a link (&ldquo;&lt;a>&rdquo; tag) to each of the sites you cite,
paragraph (&lt;p>) tags, etc. Your page should validate, and your
use of tags should make sense semantically. Use the &lt;img> tag to
include a screenshot of each page you mention.</li>
</ol>


<p>When you&rsquo;re done, put everything into one directory (your HTML page
plus any image files you used) and submit it to me using Dropbox
before the start of class on Tuesday.</p>

<ol>
<li>Suggested reading: Chapter 10, &ldquo;HTML Intro&rdquo; in &ldquo;Interact With Web
Standards&rdquo;. Refer to subsequent chapters as needed.</li>
</ol>

